---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What services does Buzz and Bee Digital provide?",
    answer:
      "We provide end-to-end digital solutions, specifically focusing on custom Design (UI/UX, branding), Development (web apps, static sites, eCommerce), and Digital Marketing (SEO, PPC, Social Media).",
  },
  {
    question: "How do you determine the cost of a project?",
    answer:
      "Every project is unique. Our development services start from $500, but the final cost depends on the project's scope, complexity, and timeline. After our initial meeting and research, we will provide you with a transparent estimate.",
  },
  {
    question: "What is your typical turnaround time?",
    answer:
      "For standard design and development tasks, we typically deliver initial concepts within 3-5 business days. Larger or more complex applications may take several weeks. We establish a clear timeline during the kickoff phase.",
  },
  {
    question: "How do we communicate during a project?",
    answer:
      "We believe in transparent and continuous communication. We use tools like Slack, Email, and regular video calls (Google Meet/Zoom) to ensure you are always updated on our progress.",
  },
  {
    question: "Do you work with international clients?",
    answer:
      "Yes, absolutely! While our core team is based in Bangladesh, we successfully serve clients globally and easily accommodate different time zones to keep the project moving smoothly.",
  },
];
---

<section>
  <div class="px-8 py-12 max-w-xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-4xl tracking-tight text-base-900 text-balance font-medium">
      The answers to the most <span class="block"
        >popular frequent questions</span
      >
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-base-600">
      Can't find your answer? Send an
      <a
        class="text-blue-500 hover:text-base-900 duration-200"
        href="mailto:buzzandbee25@gmail.com"
      >
        email
      </a>
      and our team will get back to you promptly.
    </p>

    <div
      class="mt-8 bg-white rounded-3xl text-base-900 divide-y divide-base-100"
    >
      {
        faqs.map((faq, i) => (
          <details class="px-8 py-6 group">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer text-sm font-medium  flex justify-between items-center">
              {faq.question}
              <svg
                class="size-4 ml-2 transform transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M5.23 7.21a.75.75 0 011.06.02L10 10.939l3.71-3.71a.75.75 0 111.06 1.06l-4.24 4.24a.75.75 0 01-1.06 0l-4.24-4.24a.75.75 0 01.02-1.06z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"
                />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-base-600">{faq.answer}</p>
          </details>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
